        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 18:15",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". There is an intimate connection between the retention of a private[833] and that of a public offence, and so also in the case of remission. See ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 18:15-35",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Our Lord teaches that His disciples can bind and loose the sins of their neighbours in His name; see ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 18:20",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Neither is it totally void of effect when they, even for their own sake, through anger, bind and hold the offences of their brethren.",
